</CENTER></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V1><H4>1</H4></TD><TD><P>Lo, mine 
eye hath seen all this, mine ear hath heard and understood it.</P></TD></TR><TR>
<TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V2><H4>2</H4></TD><TD><P>What ye know, the same do I     
know also: I am not inferior unto you.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A       
NAME=V3><H4>3</H4></TD><TD><P>Surely I would speak to the SHADDAY, and I desire 
to reason with EL.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V4><H4>4</H4></TD>   
<TD><P>But ye are forgers of lies, ye are all physicians of no value.</P></TD>  
</TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V5><H4>5</H4></TD><TD><P>O that ye would        
altogether hold your peace! and it should be your wisdom.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD  
VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V6><H4>6</H4></TD><TD><P>Hear now my reasoning, and hearken  
to the pleadings of my lips.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V7><H4>    
7</H4></TD><TD><P>Will ye speak wickedly for El? and talk deceitfully for       
him?</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V8><H4>8</H4></TD><TD><P>Will ye   
accept his person? will ye contend for El?</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A   
NAME=V9><H4>9</H4></TD><TD><P>Is it good that he should search you out? or as   
one man mocketh another, do ye so mock him?</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A  
NAME=V10><H4>10</H4></TD><TD><P>He will surely reprove you, if ye do secretly   
accept persons.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V11><H4>11</H4></TD><TD>
<P>Shall not his excellency make you afraid? and his dread fall upon you?</P>   
</TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V12><H4>12</H4></TD><TD><P>Your            
remembrances are like unto ashes, your bodies to bodies of clay.</P></TD></TR>  
<TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V13><H4>13</H4></TD><TD><P>Hold your peace, let me   
alone, that I may speak, and let come on me what will.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD     
VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V14><H4>14</H4></TD><TD><P>Wherefore do I take my flesh in   
my teeth, and put my life in mine hand?</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A      
NAME=V15><H4>15</H4></TD><TD><P>Though he slay me, yet will I trust in him: but 
I will maintain mine own ways before him.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A    
NAME=V16><H4>16</H4></TD><TD><P>He also shall be my salvation: for an hypocrite 
shall not come before him.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V17><H4>     
17</H4></TD><TD><P>Hear diligently my speech, and my declaration with your      
ears.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V18><H4>18</H4></TD><TD><P>Behold 
now, I have ordered my cause; I know that I shall be justified.</P></TD></TR>   
<TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V19><H4>19</H4></TD><TD><P>Who is he that will plead 
with me? for now, if I hold my tongue, I shall give up the ghost.</P></TD></TR> 
<TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V20><H4>20</H4></TD><TD><P>Only do not two things    
unto me: then will I not hide myself from thee.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP>
<A NAME=V21><H4>21</H4></TD><TD><P>Withdraw thine hand far from me: and let not 
thy dread make me afraid.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V22><H4>      
22</H4></TD><TD><P>Then call thou, and I will answer: or let me speak, and      
answer thou me.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V23><H4>23</H4></TD><TD>
<P>How many are mine iniquities and sins? make me to know my transgression and  
my sin.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V24><H4>24</H4></TD><TD><P>     
Wherefore hidest thou thy face, and holdest me for thine enemy?</P></TD></TR>   
<TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V25><H4>25</H4></TD><TD><P>Wilt thou break a leaf    
driven to and fro? and wilt thou pursue the dry stubble?</P></TD></TR><TR><TD   
VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V26><H4>26</H4></TD><TD><P>For thou writest bitter things    
against me, and makest me to possess the iniquities of my youth.</P></TD></TR>  
<TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V27><H4>27</H4></TD><TD><P>Thou puttest my feet also 
in the stocks, and lookest narrowly unto all my paths; thou settest a print     
upon the heels of my feet.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V28><H4>     
28</H4></TD><TD><P>And he, as a rotten thing, consumeth, as a garment that is   
